===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''bison'' "wild [[ox]]," borrowed from Proto-Germanic ''*wisand-'' "aurochs".

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪsən|-aɪsən]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|bison}}

# A [[wild]] [[ox]], ''[[Bison bonasus]]''.
# A similar [[American]] animal, ''[[Bison bison]] else Bos Americanus or Bisonte americano''; erroneously called a [[buffalo]].
